Git and Github Workshop 2022

https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19%3aa012c782fe2d428ab5bf644ef564efe5%40thread.tacv2/1642880345796?context=%7b%22Tid%22%3a%2271dbb522-5704-4537-9f25-6ad2dcd4278d%22%2c%22Oid%22%3a%224bd75060-ab4e-46a5-b7a9-592729886a35%22%7d

2PM - 5PM
1/23/22, 1:32 PM - Shubham Industrial Kgp Dhanbad Jharkhand: No prerequisite, ryt ??
1/23/22, 1:33 PM - Likhith IM: Nope,u need to install few software that's it
1/23/22, 1:33 PM - Likhith IM: Hello KGPians!

If you always wanted to contribute to open source projects and participate in events like GSoC/KWoC but were not sure how to, starting with a version control system would be a good way.

We at Kharagpur Open Source Society bring to you the perfect opportunity —  Git and GitHub Workshop.

Time: 2:00 to 5:00 pm
Date: 23rd January (Sunday)

It will be an interactive hands-on session detailing the nitty-gritty of open source contributions using Git and GitHub.

𝐓𝐡𝐞 𝐰𝐨𝐫𝐤𝐬𝐡𝐨𝐩 𝐰𝐢𝐥𝐥 𝐛𝐞 𝐜𝐨𝐧𝐝𝐮𝐜𝐭𝐞𝐝 𝐨𝐧 𝐌𝐢𝐜𝐫𝐨𝐬𝐨𝐟𝐭 𝐓𝐞𝐚𝐦𝐬 𝐩𝐥𝐚𝐭𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐦. 𝐃𝐨 𝐣𝐨𝐢𝐧 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐭𝐞𝐚𝐦 𝐛𝐞𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐞𝐡𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐮𝐬𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐭𝐞𝐚𝐦 𝐜𝐨𝐝𝐞: 𝐝𝟓𝟏𝐣𝐮𝟐𝐪

Please install Git on your system and have a GitHub account ready. The instructions for the same are available at
https://github.com/kossiitkgp/Git-and-GitHub-Workshop-2022/blob/main/installation.md

If reading doesn't suit you, here is a short tutorial to install Git on:
Windows: https://youtu.be/IzzAoohodPs
Linux: https://youtu.be/gdgravCh_Bw
Mac: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F02LEVYEmQw

If you still face any issues, we will be helping you from 1:30 PM to 2:00 PM on the day of the workshop.
Hoping to see you there :)

2/2/22, 4:20 PM - Devansh Gupta IM: dvar float+ x;
dvar float+ y;

dexpr float z=50*x+40*y;

maximize z;

subject to{
  c1:3*x+5*y<=150;
  c2:y<=40;
  c3:8*x+5*y<=300;
  
}
execute{
  writeln("OBJECTIVE: ",cplex.getObjValue());
   writeln("Value of x:",x);
   writeln("Value of y:",y);
   writeln("Reduced cost of x: ",x.reducedCost);
   writeln("Reduced cost of y: ",y.reducedCost);
   writeln("Dual of Constraint1: ",c1.dual);
   writeln("Dual of Constraint2: ",c2.dual);
   writeln("Dual of Constraint3: ",c3.dual);
   writeln("Slack of contraint1: ",c1.slack);
   writeln("Slack of contraint2: ",c2.slack);
   writeln("Slack of contraint3: ",c3.slack);
}

A test on 15.2.22 (Tuesday) from 12:00-1:00pm will be held. The syllabus for the test is as follows:

Definition of Laplace Transform, linearity property, conditions for existence of Laplace Transform. First and second shifting properties, Laplace Transform of derivatives and integrals, unit step functions, Dirac delta-function, error function and other special functions. Differentiation and integration of transforms, convolution theorem, inversion, periodic functions.  Applications: Evaluation of integrals by Laplace Transform. Solution of initial and boundary value problems.

Pl note this and start preparing.
R K Pandey

2/11/22, 7:03 PM - Likhith IM: Greetings,

We hope this email finds you in good health!!

To assess the Campus Residential status of the UG Students of 2020 batch, willingness to come to campus, and the duration during which you would like to come, we would like you to provide the relevant details in the form below:

https://forms.gle/Rk1nYJLm1KfVPMpZ7

Description of the Survey: This survey can help us understand the statistics of the following three types of students, whose data can be helpful for us in planning the Calling back process in the future subject to Quarantine facilities available,
1. Students who are presently residing on campus
2. Students who have a permanent room of the residence and has left to home in the recent Lockdown phase
3. Students who have not yet arrived on Campus at least once and are willing to come back on Campus

Guidelines of the Survey: This survey form should be filled by all the UG students till the 2019 batch, by 12-02-2022.

Purpose of the Survey: This survey is for data collection and should not be considered the confirmation for your calling back on campus. However, your genuine response can help us understand the residential dynamics of the students, which can further drive us to call back as many students as possible with maximum safety.

Note: This form is not meant for forwarding or sharing with any other students or groups. Contact Aditi Singhania, UG Representative(ugrep@hijli.iitkgp.ac.in) for further queries/assistance.


Best wishes,
Devaki Nandana,
VP, TSG.

2/12/22, 10:37 PM - Likhith IM: Dear Student,

This note is to appraise you about the calling of students to IIT Kharagpur. In this regard, it may be mentioned that the third wave of covid infection delayed our plans to recall students in last month (January). This month (February), we are calling students of senior UG, PG and research scholar batches, who are willing to join the campus.

From next month (March), we shall be in a position to permit the entry of UG and PG students of the 2020 batch, who are not in the campus at the moment (and those who are voluntarily willing to come - no compulsion). Following this, we shall allow the 2021 (Autumn) batch research scholars to enter the campus. Once this is done, we shall plan to bring the following batches of UG, PG and research scholars.

Since the students allowed entry to the campus would be required to pass through a quarantine/isolation phase before taking up their rooms at their designated Halls, the influx of students per week would be limited to the number of quarantine/isolation available at that point of time. Hence, we request the students planning to join the campus to bear patience till their call is announced. For clarifications, kindly email to the corresponding student representatives.

Thank you,

Dhrubajyoti Sen
Dean (Student Affairs)

3/9/22, 12:54 PM - Manav IM: Mass mailing to director and deans at 2 pm today (9-3-22) about *Unfair offline exams*
director@iitkgp.ac.in
deansa@hijli.iitkgp.ac.in
deanbtbs@iitkgp.ac.in
deanfoea@iitkgp.ac.in
deanfos@iitkgp.ac.in
deaninfra@adm.iitkgp.ac.in
deanor@iitkgp.ac.in
deansr@adm.iitkgp.ac.in
adeanbtbsb@iitkgp.ac.in
vptsg@hijli.iitkgp.ac.in

Respected sir,
The vast majority of students are facing these issues with offline exams. The students and their parents have many issues regarding offline exams. The overall students' opinion is - 'it is unfair to have offline exams'.
1.	A lot of us reside at very large distances (more than 2000kms) therefore coming to campus only for 2 weeks is absurd. What about the students who are having financial issues and need to spend money just to give offline exams
2.	We all had online lab sessions on a simulator. How are we supposed to give lab exams physically on hardware when we are taught it on a simulator.
3.	Train tickets are almost unavailable. Flight tickets are extremely expensive (the ones within these 30 days).
4.	At a time when there is hyperinflation and wealth in hand has decreased for 84% of households in India, expecting students to dish out money in such economic uncertainty just for two weeks is highly unacceptable.

5.	It is unfair to immediately conduct offline exams after 3 and a half online semesters with continuous evaluation.
6.	What about the situation for the rise in cases after the inflow of students as evident from the past.
7.	Few of us haven’t completed our vaccination. Some of us have our second dose due in April.
8.	Students and their parents are hesitant about whether the institute can manage the possible covid surge when a huge number of UG students arrive on campus. The last time they tried, they failed miserably.
9.	A lot of us haven’t visited the campus for the past two years. So, traveling and adjusting will take a lot of time during the sem and will lead to missing classes.
there are many more problems which are listed in this doc - 
https://docs.google.com/document/d/10EaIpALho72ZqOCwobjTuxVy9jPMCLT9g3jTwO-AiTY/edit?usp=sharing
Several students have genuine problems. I request you to consider the opinion of students and their parents while making the decision about offline exams.

3/9/22, 4:10 PM - Shubham Industrial Kgp Dhanbad Jharkhand: from pulp import *

prob= LpProblem("today's problem 9th march",LpMaximize)

x1=LpVariable("x1",lowBound=0)

x2=LpVariable("x2",lowBound=0)

x3=LpVariable("x3",lowBound=0)

x4=LpVariable("x4",lowBound=0)

prob+=x1+2*x2+3*x3+4*x4<=40

prob+=2*x1-x2+x3+2*x4<=8

prob+=4*x1-2*x2+x3-x4<=10

prob+=2*x1+x2-3*x3+5*x4

#prob+=8*x1+6*x2+3*x3-2*x4

output=prob.solve()

print(LpStatus[output])

print("the objective function's value is",prob.objective.value())

print("the value of x1 is: ",value(x1))

print("the value of x2 is: ",value(x2))

print("the value of x3 is: ",value(x2))

print("the value of x4 is: ",value(x4))

3/11/22, 2:13 PM - Manav IM: *Mass mailing to director and deans at 2 pm today (11-3-22)*

about *Unfair offline exams*
director@iitkgp.ac.in
deansa@hijli.iitkgp.ac.in
deanbtbs@iitkgp.ac.in
deanfoea@iitkgp.ac.in
deanfos@iitkgp.ac.in
deaninfra@adm.iitkgp.ac.in
deanor@iitkgp.ac.in
deansr@adm.iitkgp.ac.in
adeanbtbsb@iitkgp.ac.in
vptsg@hijli.iitkgp.ac.in

Respected sir,
The vast majority of students are facing these issues with offline exams. The students and their parents have many issues regarding offline exams. The overall students' opinion is - 'it is unfair to have offline exams'.
1. A lot of us reside at very large distances (more than 2000kms) therefore coming to campus only for 2 weeks is absurd. What about the students who are having financial issues and need to spend money just to give offline exams
2. We all had online lab sessions on a simulator. How are we supposed to give lab exams physically on hardware when we are taught it on a simulator.
3. Train tickets are almost unavailable. Flight tickets are extremely expensive (the ones within these 30 days).
4. At a time when there is hyperinflation and wealth in hand has decreased for 84% of households in India, expecting students to dish out money in such economic uncertainty just for two weeks is highly unacceptable.

5. It is unfair to immediately conduct offline exams after 3 and a half online semesters with continuous evaluation.
6. What about the situation for the rise in cases after the inflow of students as evident from the past.
7. Few of us haven’t completed our vaccination. Some of us have our second dose due in April.
8. Students and their parents are hesitant about whether the institute can manage the possible covid surge when a huge number of UG students arrive on campus. The last time they tried, they failed miserably.
9. A lot of us haven’t visited the campus for the past two years. So, traveling and adjusting will take a lot of time during the sem and will lead to missing classes.
there are many more problems which are listed in this doc - 
https://docs.google.com/document/d/10EaIpALho72ZqOCwobjTuxVy9jPMCLT9g3jTwO-AiTY/edit?usp=sharing
Several students have genuine problems. I request you to consider the opinion of students and their parents while making the decision about offline exams.

Share this post as much as possible 

In this video, when a student from IIT Kharagpur called Kundan Nath, Under secretary government of India(Ministry of Education) , he said "Ministry of Education haven't said anything about examination whether it should be online or offline.We have just conveyed the guidelines about the reopening of the Institutes. The decision of whether the exams should be taken online or offline is to be decided by the concerned institutes. There are no orders or guidelines of compulsory offline exam to the institutes. Ministry doesn't interfere in IIT's matters. "
 
This statement of Under Secretary to government of India totally differs from prof Rintu Banerjee, HOD Agricultural and Food Engineering. who said( in the mail to students, ss of which is attached to this post) - "As HoD, I am confirming you all that as per the ministry's guidelines there will be no online examination henceforth." Students have been hearing the statements like this also from the authorities and professors that Ministries guidelines are responsible for compulsory offline exam in IIT Kharagpur.

Official contact number of Under Secretary is visible in this video and anyone can verify that it's his official contact number. To verify his post and contact number, screenshot of his letter to All IITs is attached in this post. Also in this PDF
-https://drive.google.com/file/d/1Goc7qdhBPfzNquH_8PnO_2l-ST7dLk4r/view?usp=drivesdk

It seems that Institute has even started  lying to its students to force them for writing offline exam because Under secretary himself has said that Ministry of Education has not given any order regarding offline exams.

Students are disappointed with the authorities of IIT Kharagpur foe this. Authorities are not considering students problems and huge number of students having these problems while taking the decision of compulsory offline exam. Students of IIT Kharagpur are against compulsory offline exam.
Students are repeatedly mailing the authorities but no steps have been taken by the authorities. Authorities are not having a meetings with student senate. Director and authorities are not replying any of  students' mails. Students don't have much time left before 31st March deadline for coming to campus, also there are very few days left for offline exam. We request the authorities to announce their final decision on compulsory offline exam as soon as possible. 


Follow, like this fb acc for more updates - http://facebook.com/iit.kgps.voice

3/16/22, 3:07 PM - Ankit Industrial KGP Patna: import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pylab as plt
import seaborn as sns
import pulp as p
import random

#Get the Node Locations
location = pd.read_excel("C:/Users/Ankit/Desktop/OR Lab/PuLP/DataFile.xlsx","Nodes",index_col=0)
Y = location.columns.values[0]
X = location.columns.values[1]

n_point = len(location)

#Get the Distance Matrix
data = pd.read_excel("C:/Users/Ankit/Desktop/OR Lab/PuLP/DataFile.xlsx","Distance Matrix", index_col=0)

#Vehicle Depot is assumed to be the first Node
#from where the Salesman starts the Journey

vehicle_depot = 0

# Draw the problem state

for i, row in location.iterrows():

    if i == vehicle_depot: 
        plt.scatter(row [X], row[Y], c='r')
        plt.text(row[X] +0.33, row [Y] +0.33, 'eV_Depot')

    else:
        plt.scatter(row [X], row[Y], c='black')
        plt.text(row [X] + 0.33, row [Y] +0.33, f'{1}')

plt.title('Node Points: id')

plt.xlabel (X)

plt.ylabel (Y)

plt.show()

# Set the problem

prob=p.LpProblem("MIP_TSP_Minimize_Small",p.LpMinimize)

# Set Variables

x = p.LpVariable.dicts('x',((i,j) for i in range(n_point) for j in range(n_point)), lowBound=0, upBound=1, cat='Binary')

# Set Objective Function

prob+=p.lpSum(data.iloc [i,j]*x[i,j] for i in range(n_point) for j in range(n_point))

# Set Constraints

for i in range(n_point):
    prob+=x[i,i]==0 
    prob+=p.lpSum(x[i,j] for j in range(n_point))==1 
    prob+=p.lpSum(x[j,i] for j in range(n_point))==1



#print("import success")

Hello KGPians!

We are super stoked to announce the launch of CDC companion! 

Having observed the nuances of CDC preparation, we felt the need for a structured and centralised platform to help students prepare for CDC internships. Therefore we bring to you the CDC Companion platform which aims to help students in planning their preparation efficiently and getting all the help required in a centralised manner. 

We are excited to hear from you. If you have any feedback or suggestions/issues with the platform, feel free to reach out to us at cdc.companion@gmail.com. We really hope to help everyone ace their CDC journey and will keep updating the platform as and when need be.

Cheers and all the best!

4/24/22, 12:59 PM - Biswa Ranjan Barik IM: So I tell you the positives and the negatives - 

POSITIVES 

1) Opening of options - You learn finance - you get familiar with the jargon, firms like Nomura might give you an edge for internships and placements
2) The course curriculum is similar to the syllabus for exams such as FRM/CFA so it might get relatively easier to get a certification
3) Diversifies your knowledge pool - If you're someone who doesn't learn well online through coursera and needs deadlines or external push to spend time studying - opting for FP might help (Also coz they're counted in your depth so you gotta prep - hence it's not the same as opting for additional courses). So FP does help you add qn extra knowledge vertical there.

NEGATIVES -

1) FP is hectic. It kinda gives a lot of workload in your 8th sem when everyone else is chilling. You kinda want to relax but since the professors are used to teaching business school students, they are used to giving many assignments and repititive tests and extending classes - Something 4th year UG's don't appreciate much.

2) Closing(?) of options - If you're a ranker in Indu (even among 5 year Indu people), FMCG firms such as HUL do shortlist you. However it is said that having an FP tag can make firm thinks that the student is likely to enter into IB's in the long run anyway so they don't shortlist. Many including myself have suffered this negative bias during CDC internship placements. In general, even Econ students suffer the same bias. So choosing Finance might narrow down your career options to just IBs and the like.

3) Opportunity cost - Indu is a strong department and it also gives you a lot of flexibility to opt for multiple breadths. With FP, all your breadths become compulsory depth courses. So you might have to study courses that don't like as much.

4/27/22, 1:23 AM - +91 88794 53459: Product roles are a combination of tech and strategy.
You will mainly be working for a company and your job will be to conceptualise new features for their existing products. Many times it is less of a tech, and more off a strategy role. For example, if you're working for a crypto-investment app company... they will ask questions like what can we do to increase the Weekly Average Users of the app or how to increase the transaction frequency, etc...
Good knowledge of Business Strategy and prior experience in case studies is essential.

8/27/22, 2:33 PM - Deepa Industrial Kgp West Bengal: 𝐎𝐩𝐩𝐮𝐭𝐮𝐧𝐢𝐭𝐢𝐞𝐬 𝐚𝐭 𝐈𝐒𝐄(𝐏𝐫𝐨𝐠𝐫𝐚𝐦𝐦𝐞 𝐈𝐃:𝐈𝐈𝐓/𝐂𝐄𝐏/𝐖𝐎𝐑/𝐖𝐎𝐑/𝟐𝟎𝟐𝟐-𝟐𝟎𝟐𝟑/𝐈𝐌/𝟕𝟒)
Department of Industrial and Systems Engineering, IIT Kharagpur, presents a free webinar for BE/BTech students and working professionals who aspire for higher studies (MTech/MS/PhD) in the areas related to Industrial Engineering, Systems Engineering and Management. There are multiple opportunities starting from short-term internships to long term project positions, various post graduate and research degree programs at this department. Due to its interdisciplinary nature, students from all Engineering backgrounds are welcome to participate in this webinar. You will get a unique opportunity to interact with IIT professors and the current students, and understand the career prospects and the scope of employment in this prestigious department of IIT Kharagpur.
𝐓𝐡𝐞 𝐥𝐚𝐬𝐭 𝐝𝐚𝐭𝐞 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐫𝐞𝐠𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐫𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐢𝐬 𝟏𝟓𝐭𝐡 𝐒𝐞𝐩, 𝟐𝟎𝟐𝟐. 𝐑𝐞𝐠𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐫𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐢𝐬 𝐟𝐫𝐞𝐞, 𝐛𝐮𝐭 𝐦𝐚𝐧𝐝𝐚𝐭𝐨𝐫𝐲 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐩𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐢𝐜𝐢𝐩𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧.
  https://erp.iitkgp.ac.in/CEP/courses.htm
For any query, contact the student chairman, Deepak Kushwaha <deepak78888@iitkgp.ac.in>

9/2/22, 9:15 PM - Likhith IM: Hello everyone!
This is regarding a pilot research study that is being undertaken to understand the *‘perception on mind and mental health among the student population of the Indian Institute of Technology Kharagpur (IIT KGP)'.* This research will help us build the larger literature base on this topic along with providing insights and recommendations on enriching the overall quality of our minds.

 _You are eligible to participate if:_ 
 • You are between 18-26 years of age
 • Pursuing an undergraduate or a postgraduate degree at IIT KGP
An Indian Citizen

 _If you decide to participate in this significant study, please note that:_ 
 • You will be required for face-to-face interaction with us based on mutual convenience. The interaction should take about 30-45 minutes.
 • The interaction will be recorded purely for research purposes.

Please convey your interest/consent for participation *by tomorrow* by filling up the Google form below or you may contact the numbers that is given below. The interviews will be held later before 6th September, 2022 at your convenience.

Your contribution to the research will be extremely valuable. *Kindly, fill out the form below to participate:* 

 https://forms.gle/xs1d5uzKxNpHRyS28
           OR 
You may directly contact  the numbers  given below.

Regards,
 _Shreya Chakraborty (8777597066),_
_Swati Semwal (8130703264),_
_Kaptan Bairwa (8619685907)_ 
 *Interns, Indian Knowledge System (IKS) at AICTE,* 
 *Ministry of Education, Govt. of India*

9/20/22, 12:02 AM - +91 88794 53459: Yes. And he mentioned autocorrelation should be low. But didn't teach what that meant
9/20/22, 12:13 AM - +91 88794 53459: Just generate 1 million random number pairs (X, Y)... each pair denotes a coordinate in a unit square.

Then generate 1 million more random numbers (Z). For each of them, count the number of previously generated points such that X<Z and Y<Z. The value of Z for which number of such points is closest to 130,000 gives us the solution.

9/20/22, 1:32 PM - Ankit Industrial KGP Patna: For estimating any sqrt(a), initialise cnt to 0 & run for max_iterations number of iterations:

1. Generate a random numbers r in the range [0,a] (generate bw 0&1 and product with a)
2. If r*r<a, cnt+=1


Value of cnt/max_iterations gives sqrt(a)/a

9/22/22, 2:20 AM - Biswa Ranjan Barik IM: Define measure analysis improve control
9/22/22, 2:21 AM - Biswa Ranjan Barik IM: As a methodology, six sigma may be viewed as the collection of the following steps or
phases: define, measure, analyze, improve, and control. Within each phase there are certain
toolsthat could be utilized. Some ofthe tools are discussed in this chapter.In the define phase
customer needs are translated to specific attributes that are critical to meeting such needs.
Typically, these are categorized in terms of critical to quality, delivery, or cost. Identification
of these attributes will create a framework for study. For example, suppose that the waiting
time of customersin a bank isthe problem to be tackled. The number of tellers on duty during
specific periods in the day is an attribute that is critical to reducing the waiting time, which
might be a factor of investigation.
The measure phase consists of identifying metricsfor process performance. Thisincludes
theestablishment of baselinelevelsaswell. In ourexample,achosenmetriccould betheaverage
waitingtimepriortoservice,inminutes,whilethebaselinelevelcouldbethecurrentvalueofthis
metric,say 5 minutes. Key process input and output variables are also identified. In the define
phase, some tools could be the process flowcharts or its detailed version, the process map. To
identifythe vital few fromthe trivialmany, aPareto chart could be appropriate. Further,to study
the variousfactorsthat may affect an outcome, a cause-and-effect diagram may be used.In the
measure phase, onefirst hastoensurethatthemeasurement systemitselfis stable. Thetechnical
QUALITY FUNCTION DEPLOYMENT 99
name for such a study is gage repeatability and reproducibility. Thereafter, benchmark
measures of process capability could be utilized,some of which are defects per unit of product,
parts permillion nonconforming,and rolledthroughout yield, representingthe proportion ofthe
final product that has no defects. Other measures of process capability are discussed later in a
separate chapter.
In the analyze phase, the objective is to determine which of a multitude of factors affects
the output variable (s) significantly, through analysis of collected data. Tools may be simple
graphical toolssuch asscatterplots and multivari charts. Alternatively, analytical models may
be built linking the output or response variable to one of more independent variablesthrough
regression analysis. Hypothesis testing on selected parameters (i.e., average waiting time
before and after process improvement) could be pursued. Analysis-of-variance techniques
may be used to investigate the statistical significance of one or more factors on the response
variable.
The improve phase consists of identifying the factor levels of significant factors to
optimize the performancemeasure chosen, which could be tominimize,maximize, or achieve
a goal value. In our example, the goal could be to minimize the average waiting time of
customersin the bank subject to certain resource or other process constraints. Here, concepts
in design of experiments are handy tools.
Finally, the control phase deals with methods to sustain the gains identified in the
preceding phase. Methods of statistical process control using control charts, discussed extensivelyinlaterchapters,arecommontools.Processcapabilitymeasuresarealsomeaningfulin
this phase. They may provide a relative index of the degree to which the improved
product, process, or service meets established norms based on customer requirements
